Paul Edward Graf, 45 years old, was named president and chief executive officer of this closely held concern.
He most recently was a partner at a New York venture capital affiliate of Schroders PLC, London.
He is also the past president and chief executive of Conrac Corp., which was acquired by Mark IV Industries Inc. in 1987.
Mr. Graf succeeds Vernon R. Anderson, 58, who remains vice chairman and has held the Axel posts on an interim basis.
Axel is an oil exploration and production, trading and marketing, engineered products, electronics and metals concern. 

